Let me directly examine the bug. Looking at the `getRelativePositionByQName()` method:

```java
/**
 * Get relative position of this among like-named siblings.
 * @return 1..n
 */
private int getRelativePositionByQName() {
    int count = 1;
    Node n = node.getPreviousSibling();
    while (n != null) {
        if (n.getNodeType() == Node.ELEMENT_NODE) {
            String nm = n.getNodeName();
            if (nm.equals(node.getNodeName())) {
            count++;
            }
        }
        n = n.getPreviousSibling();
    }
    return count;
}
```

This method compares `nm.equals(node.getNodeName())` which compares the full name with prefix (e.g., "a:elem" vs "b:elem"), but it should compare local name and namespace URI to determine if they are the same type of element.

